name: Honey-Chipotle Chicken
author: Randy
summary: Shredded chicken in a honey-chipotle sauce that I usually use in burritos.
ingredients: 6  skinless, boneless chicken breasts, or more to taste
2 (15 ounce) cans black beans, drained and rinsed
directions: Blend honey, garlic, and chipotle peppers in adobo sauce together in a food processor until smooth
Place chicken breasts in the bottom of a slow cooker and mix in honey-chipotle sauce
Cook in the slow cooker on Low for 5 hours
Transfer chicken to a bowl and shred using 2 forks
Return chicken to the slow cooker and stir in black beans
Continue to cook on Low until cooked through, about 30 minutes more
